Those who are accountable will be known.

as the Queen of Secrets commands...

Gain a new perspective and be released from uncertainty.

Oh you'll love the card I have next...
P L E A S U R E.

I see Destruction. Upheaval, Chaos, and the Shattering of Belief.
A fresh start. After the darkest hour comes the dawn of a new day.
The dead perhaps will take opportunity now.
The Queen of Secrets has blessed me today.
I love this card like I love her.
The card of Darkness, Illusion, and the Unconscious.
Do not hide your truest self.

Is this stupid thing even working?
Hit. Jesus man, are you fuckin' psychic or something?
Nah, I'm just lucky, I swear. There's cooler stuff I could be doing if I were pyschic.
Hit. See you could be psychic too.
He was wearing a leather jacket.
He went out looking for supplies and he hasn't come back,
If anyone see's him, please let me know.
If my wife is listening, I just wanted to say, I'm ok.
I just got held up by a pack of biters.
*Soft but audible voice can be heard*
Hurry up! We gotta leave before more of them show up!
Jess... if you can hear me, we are heading to <bzzt>
Ah who cares- can't be but a handful of you left
I think this might be it.
So I've gone ahead and decided I'd take this time to play some songs
Maybe <Kzzzt> somber since <Kzzzzzzt> only thing I feel <Kzzzt> days.
I am... er was a priest
*the audible sound of a shotgun being loaded*
I have been held out in my residence
I give the blessings of god, if he still resides up in heaven upon all who have faith
*several loud cracks of shotgun fire followed by infected groans*
Hello there, I had a thought a while ago...
What is the one good thing that has come with this waking hell?
Some would say not having to be pursued by bills.
Others would say not having to come to the "shit hole" they call their job.
For me, the one thing I look forward to each passing day is the freedom.
The freedom that allows me to not have to worry about the old world responsibilities.
Those responsibilities that had held me down, taking me away from our natural home.
The same home that we had all evolved from, grown up in, and will most likely die from.
This feeling of euphoria however, comes with a great and terrible price...
*shuffling of papers, followed by something hitting the floor*
I told you this would happen.
And now look at me. I'm safe.
Food to last for years. Water, too.
Take that, lizard people! Take that, CIA!
Now nobody will call me crazy...
Just needed to get this out there, wouldn’t be right without sending out some sort of warning.
I’ve been on the run from a herd for the last hour, still haven’t shaken them yet.
I’m leading them through <KRRRRZT>, hoping to go in through the front door of a house, quietly slip out the back.
Hopefully they’re dumb enough to think I’m inside and break in by the time I’m long gone.
If you’re in <KRRRRRZT>, just be aware, you’re gonna be dealing with bigger crowds than normal.
Staying away for a while’s probably the best option.
If you can hear me, I need help. Those – things… they found me.
I’m in my farmhouse outside <KRRRRZT>... Address is <KRRRZZT>.
They’re tearing down my barricades… I’m hiding in the attic.
I was able to move my supplies up here, I have enough food to last me a few days, but…
When they get inside and don’t find me, odds are they’re just gonna stay put.
If you can take them out or lead them away, I’ll give you half of whatever I have.
Is there anyone out there? Hello?
I- I need help. The deadheads chased me into the <KRRRRZT> just outside <KRZZZT>.
Had to hide in the walk-in until they passed through, but now I can’t get out.
The handle broke off when I tried to open it. Been here for the last two days.
Look, I don’t have much, but if you can get me out of here, I’ll make it worth your while.
If you can hear this, don’t come into town.
A mob of those things is moving through. Hundreds at least.
They’re tearing through every building. They spot you, you’ll have one hell of a time getting away.
Gotta keep quiet, had to hide in a dumpster, hope they move through without noticing me.
I got cut off running from them. Had no choice.
To anyone on this frequency, odds are you’ve heard the gunshots.
Keep away. We’re clearing out the dead in town.
It’ll take a few hours to wrap up, and we’d appreciate if you made our jobs simple.
Just let us do our job, and your lives will become a whole hell of a lot easier.
All is dead. All is red. Red means dead. Dead means red.
The walls. Floors. Ceilings. ALL IS RED!
RED! RED! ALL I SEE! IS RED!!!
...John, if you can hear this, it's Ash...
...you need to get out of there.
They're coming, and I don't know how long you have...
...they killed Chris and took the truck...
...I'm sorry I can't be there with you...
...can't even believe it's taken this long...
...do you think they're actually gonna go away?
I hope so...how long have I been up here?
Think you could catch a bottle?
I'm not sure we should try, the street is pretty wide.
...let's just wait it out. They always wander off eventually.
Ugh. Yeah, put it on the pile.
God damn, Silas, what the hell. Yeah, put it on the pile.
[img=music]...I'll give you aaaaallll I've got to give... [img=music]
...there's GOTTA be more food there...are you sure you looked everywhere?
Well, we gotta figure out something. It's not just us.
You think I don't know that?
What the hell is that supposed to mean?
...can we just not do this? Not today. Not now. We're both hungry and pissed.
Fine. Whatever. I'll see you when I get back.
West Point is gone. Don't go there.
It's not as bad as the others. If you're looking for a safe haven, that might be your best bet...
...just stay the fuck away from the prison.
Gotcha. Listen...I really appreciate your help.
Just keep moving. Don't sit in one place too long.
Like I have a choice about that.
Hey, are you picking this up? It's like a sea out there...
...just heads bobbing up and down in the old Food Court.
Yeah, I'm hearing you. So you made it there?
Sure did, and if I don't get seen we'll make out like bandits here...
...man, I wish the Food Court was open.
My mouth is watering just thinking about it...
...a big ol' slice of nasty, greasy pizza...
...I miss dipping fries in mayo. I don't care if you think that's gross.
I mean...the power is still on...I bet there's still frozen food at the Spiffos on the way back...
You got it, babe. I'll be back soon.
....don't think I don't know right where you are.
You fucked up when you fucked me over.
I KNOW you can hear me.
Say something you SON OF A BITCH!!!
I'm fuckin' coming for you. Watch your ass.
...two cans of peas, three cans of corn...two pounds of peanut butter...
Two cans of peas, got it.
I don't like the orange kind.
Ok, you know what? I'm just gonna count stock when I get back.
Alright, let's make a bet. Pack a' smokes says I can get that one in the suit...
From there? No way. Not a fuckin' chance.
Yeah, sure, we got a deal. Take your shot.
Whooohoohoo....did you see that? Told ya.
Goddamn, man, you're a good shot.
You owe me a pack of smokes, asshole.
To the woman I heard asking for help, where are you?
Yeah, you're coming through! What's your location, I can come get you...
I've got a car and gas, I can help you.
How do I know I can trust you?
I guess you don't...do you want help or not?
Sheesh, I don't know how you do it.
I am so sick of sodapop.
Can't we go get some water? It's just one trip, dad...
...you know we can't. It's just not safe out there.
...I have to keep you safe. That's what mom wanted.
